# Clerk Billing (B2C)

Clerk Billing is enabled for this app. Plans and pricing are managed in the Clerk Dashboard, not in code. Stripe is used only for payment processing.

## Plans & Features

| Plan | Slug | Features |
|------|------|----------|
| Free | `free_user` | `3_deck_limit` — user may create up to 3 decks |
| Pro | `pro` | `unlimited_deck` — no deck limit | 
|  |  | `ai_flash_card_generation` — AI-powered card creation |

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component from `@clerk/nextjs` for pricing pages:

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from '@clerk/nextjs'

export default function PricingPage() {
  return <PricingTable />
}
```

## Access Control

Gate content by **Plan** or **Feature** using one of two approaches:

### Server-side: `has()` from `auth()`

```tsx
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const { has } = await auth()

  // Check by plan
  if (!has({ plan: 'pro' })) return <p>Pro subscribers only.</p>

  // Check by feature
  if (!has({ feature: 'ai_flash_card_generation' })) return <p>Upgrade to Pro for AI card generation.</p>

  return <h1>Protected Content</h1>
}
```

### Client-side: `<Show>` component

```tsx
import { Show } from '@clerk/nextjs'

// Gate by plan
<Show when={{ plan: 'pro' }} fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to access this feature.</p>}>
  <h1>Pro Content</h1>
</Show>

// Gate by feature
<Show when={{ feature: 'unlimited_deck' }} fallback={<p>Free users are limited to 3 decks.</p>}>
  <h1>Unlimited Decks</h1>
</Show>
```

## Rules

- Use `has()` for server-side access checks (Server Components, Server Actions).
- Use `<Show>` for client-side conditional rendering based on plan or feature.
- Never hardcode plan/feature slugs in multiple places — prefer constants.
- Enforce the 3-deck limit for `free_user` plans server-side before creating a new deck.
- Billing is in Beta — pin `@clerk/nextjs` and `clerk-js` versions to avoid breaking changes.
